FBIS4-9275 "dreeu078__a94051" FBIS-EEU-94-078-A Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 ANNEX Yugoslavia, Kosovo Serbian Government Closes Albanian Shops Serbian Government Closes Albanian Shops AU2104184794 Tirana ATA in English 1200 GMT 21 Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2104184794 Tirana ATA English BFN [Text] Prishtina, April 20 (ATA) -- The Serb Government is closing down the private shops of Albanians because they do not want to change the inscriptions in Albanian language on their shops. Serbs have demanded from them to put the inscriptions in the Cyrillic alphabet. They also want to change the name of Ferizaj to Uroshevac, which is a Serb name.
